tournaments.about:
Only UK players are eligible to participate in the tournament.
The winner can represent United Kingdom in the group stage of the Carcassonne Champions League 2025.
The silver and bronze medalists will earn spots in the CCL 2025 qualification.

Tournament format:

Round robin format with all duels played as a best of 3.

tournaments.about:
Ukrainian Carcassonne Online Championship (UCOC) 2025 is a national tournament in which we play on the Board Game Arena (BGA) platform, in weekly one-on-one matches in the Best of Three format.

Each season takes place once a year, organized by player divisions with promotion and relegation. Only Ukrainian players are admitted to the championship.

Dates: January 20 - April 6, 2025

In addition to enjoying the competition and the community built around Carcassonne, the winner of the top division of UCOC 2025 will get the chance to represent Ukraine in the Carcassonne Champions League 2026.

The tournament was recognized as the official Online Carcassonne Championship of Ukraine by Feelindigo, the publisher of the game in Ukraine.

tournaments.about:
The Belarusian Carcassonne Premier League (BCPL) is an online competition for the Carcassonne board game played in real time.

Only Belarusian players are allowed to participate in the tournament.

All games take place on the platform https://boardgamearena.com/

Players compete in a one-on-one round-robin format until two wins (best of 3).

The winners qualify for the offline Championship of Belarus in Carcassonne.

Carcassonne Asian Cup 2025

Start: August 2024

Seeding Pots

(according to the results of WTCOC 2025):

  • Pot 1: TBD
  • Pot 2: TBD
  • Pot 3: TBD
  • Pot 4: TBD

Tournament format

Group Stage: two groups, each team plays against all other teams in their group.
The best 2 teams from each group advance to the Playoffs:

  • Semi-finals: 1st team from one group vs 2nd team from another group
  • Match for the bronze medals
  • Grand Final

All matches are 5 vs 5 duels in a best-of-3 format.
tournaments.name: Asian Cup 2025

tournaments.about:
Start: September 16th

End: November 24th

Tournament format:

Players play one-on-one real-time duels in a best-of-3 format. Players only face one opponent each week.
The competition runs for 10 weeks, with the first 7 weeks for group matches and the last 3 weeks for the playoffs.
The top 2 players from each group advance to the quarter-finals, and from there the competition continues in a single-elimination system.
